keyFacts: The document is a travel authorization for a DOJ employee related to the U.S. v. Epstein case (docket 2018R0618).
The purpose of the travel is specifically for 'Victim Interviews'.
The travel was scheduled for July 11-14, 2019, indicating active investigative work on the case at that time.
The destination is listed only as 'L, United States', which may be a redacted or coded location.
The authorization was approved on July 10, 2019, and was pending further approval at the time of the notification.
